seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: Matchmaker Sima Taparia guides clients in the US and India in the arranged marriage process, offering an inside look at the custom in a modern era.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: Sima Taparia, everyone's favorite matchmaker, returns for another season of helping eligible, eccentric and eager clients find their future spouses.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: Sima Taparia aka Sima Aunty returns for the 3rd season in this docuseries as the matchmaker for singles from South Asia.

episodes.name: Slim, Trim and Educated
episodes.overview: Sima meets three unlucky-in-love clients: a stubborn Houston lawyer, a picky Mumbai bachelor and a misunderstood Morris Plains, N.J., event planner.

episodes.name: Just Find Me Someone!
episodes.overview: Nadia's and Aparna’s dates have mixed results. Friends and family get honest with Pradhyuman. Sima consults a face reader for clarity on her clients.

episodes.name: I’m Trying My Best!
episodes.overview: A setback with Vinay temporarily discourages Nadia. Sima offers two more prospects to Aparna. Feeling the pressure, Pradhyuman finally goes on a date.

episodes.name: I Want to See You Again
episodes.overview: Nadia has a promising date. Pradhyuman sees a life coach. Sima sends Aparna to an astrologer and seeks a cultural match for guidance counselor Vyasar.

episodes.name: Take the Elephant out of the Room
episodes.overview: A date with a model uplifts Pradhyuman. As Aparna’s luck seems to turn, Vyasar hits a snag. Akshay’s mother insists that he marry within the year.

episodes.name: It’s High Time
episodes.overview: Vyasar and Rashi instantly bond. As Akshay rejects over 70 matches, Preeti gives him an ultimatum. Progressive Ankita looks for an equal partnership.

episodes.name: Marriages Are Breaking like Biscuits
episodes.overview: Sima faces a challenge with single mother Rupam. A discovery about her match bothers Ankita. Vyasar frets over revealing his father’s past to Rashi.

episodes.name: Adjustment and Compromise
episodes.overview: Akshay makes a decision while a new path emerges for Rupam. Ankita has an empowering realization. As her clients move on, Sima’s work never stops.

1.name: Season 1
1.overview: Matchmaker Sima Taparia guides clients in the US and India in the arranged marriage process, offering an inside look at the custom in a modern era.

episodes.name: I've Dated Lots of Chicks
episodes.overview: Sima meets Akshay, a bachelor whose small-town location has hindered his search for love. Meanwhile, some of her past clients return with new hopes.

episodes.name: Be a Boss, Marry a Boss, Build an Empire
episodes.overview: Sima urges Akshay to change his thinking, and worries about Nadia and Vishal's differences. New client Viral shares her criteria for an ideal mate.

episodes.name: Ovo-lacto-semi-vegetarian
episodes.overview: Viral and Aparna each go on first dates. Concerned that his past might hamper his future, Akshay takes action. Nadia faces a surprise in California.

episodes.name: I Love You Like a Friend
episodes.overview: An old client returns — and he's not alone! Sima meets soft-spoken cardiologist Arshneel. Viral seeks a physical attraction. Aparna reflects on Daman.

episodes.name: The Looks of Clint Eastwood
episodes.overview: A date leaves Arshneel apprehensive. Aparna reaches a conclusion about her needs. Sima and new client Shital debate compromise versus settling.

episodes.name: Very Chulbuli
episodes.overview: Despite a rocky date, Viral may be smitten. Arshneel and Rinkle get off to a promising start. A charming but chatty prospect gives Shital pause.

episodes.name: All The Bases Covered
episodes.overview: After a few flat dates, Shital worries about self-sabotage. Chemistry also proves elusive for Vinesh, Sima's new client, as he meets a potential match.

episodes.name: I Feel Like He's The One
episodes.overview: Opening up to Aashay, Viral notices her softer side emerging. Still struggling to find a connection, Vinesh finally considers changing his own mindset.

2.name: Season 2
2.overview: Sima Taparia, everyone's favorite matchmaker, returns for another season of helping eligible, eccentric and eager clients find their future spouses.

episodes.name: Husband-in-Waiting
episodes.overview: In London, Priya hopes for a new start and teacher Bobby wants out of the friend zone. In New Delhi, a client returns. A happy couple ponders next steps.

episodes.name: Take the Bobby
episodes.overview: Sima meets with founders of South Asian dating apps. Bobby and Priya take a salsa class. Rushali worries a spouse will separate her from her parents.

episodes.name: An ABCD
episodes.overview: Viral meets Aashay's parents. Rushali enjoys a first date — until it hits a snag. In California, Sima urges ER doctor Vikash to rethink his criteria.

episodes.name: A Top Knot Appreciator
episodes.overview: Vikash struggles to let go of his checklist. A new prospect has Priya cautiously optimistic. A life coach helps Rushali open up.

episodes.name: Is Costco a Hobby?
episodes.overview: As Priya considers rejecting an effusive suitor, Sima pushes back. Arti seeks a match with ambition and an edge. A familiar face returns with a new glow.

episodes.name: Wills and Whims and Fancies
episodes.overview: The future looks bright for Shital and Priya. Arti begins to question Sima's outlook. Vikash and a date hit it off — but they have one big difference.

episodes.name: Daddy's Little Tall Girl
episodes.overview: Finding a match for marketing professional Pavneet may be a tall order. Through a dating app, Arti finds the spark she's seeking — but Sima is skeptical.

episodes.name: Marry Me
episodes.overview: Pavneet seeks clarity when a suitor is slow to follow up. Arti is in for a surprise. As for Sima? She remains in demand as ever.

3.name: Season 3
3.overview: Sima Taparia aka Sima Aunty returns for the 3rd season in this docuseries as the matchmaker for singles from South Asia.
